caption: Check if point is in circle radius with

AJy.caption: Checked point lat
AJy.doc: A number. Example 5.123456. Refers to the point that will be checked if it is contained by the circle.
AJy.name: point_to_be_checked_latitude

AJz.caption: Checked point lon
AJz.doc: A number. Example 5.123456. Refers to the point that will be checked if it is contained by the circle.
AJz.name: point_to_be_checked_longitude

AKA.caption: Circle center lat
AKA.doc: A number. Example 5.123456. Refers to the circle that will be used to see if the point is inside it or not.
AKA.name: circle_center_latitude

AKB.caption: Circle center lon
AKB.doc: A number. Example 5.123456. Refers to the circle that will be used to see if the point is inside it or not.
AKB.name: circle_center_longitude

AKC.caption: Circle radius
AKC.doc: A number, in meters. Example 5000 (for 5km). Refers to the circle that will be used to see if the point is inside it or not.
AKC.name: circle_radius
